# Data Access Patterns

## Data Access Layer — `src/db/queries/`

All database reads and writes must be encapsulated in helper functions inside `src/db/queries/`. Never import `db` or call Drizzle query builders directly in Server Components, Server Actions, or API routes.

Organize one file per domain entity (e.g., `src/db/queries/decks.ts`, `src/db/queries/cards.ts`).

```tsx
// src/db/queries/decks.ts
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decks } from "@/db/schema";
import { eq, and } from "drizzle-orm";

export async function getDecksByUser(userId: string) {
  return db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.userId, userId));
}

export async function getDeckByIdForUser(deckId: number, userId: string) {
  const [deck] = await db
    .select()
    .from(decks)
    .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.userId, userId)));
  return deck;
}

export async function insertDeck(data: { title: string; description?: string; userId: string }) {
  const [deck] = await db.insert(decks).values(data).returning();
  return deck;
}
```

```tsx
// src/db/queries/cards.ts
import { db } from "@/db";
import { cards, decks } from "@/db/schema";
import { eq, and } from "drizzle-orm";

// Read helpers join on `decks` to enforce ownership
export async function getCardsByDeckForUser(deckId: number, userId: string) {
  return db
    .select({ card: cards })
    .from(cards)
    .innerJoin(decks, eq(cards.deckId, decks.id))
    .where(and(eq(cards.deckId, deckId), eq(decks.userId, userId)))
    .then((rows) => rows.map((r) => r.card));
}

export async function insertCard(data: { deckId: number; front: string; back: string }) {
  const [card] = await db.insert(cards).values(data).returning();
  return card;
}
```

## Retrieval — Server Components Only

All data fetching must happen in React Server Components. Never fetch data in Client Components or via `useEffect`. Call query helpers from `@/db/queries/*` — never use `db` directly.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — inline Drizzle call in a Server Component
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decks } from "@/db/schema";

export default async function DecksPage() {
  const allDecks = await db.select().from(decks);
}

// ✅ GOOD — delegates to a query helper
import { getDecksByUser } from "@/db/queries/decks";

export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  const allDecks = await getDecksByUser(userId!);
  return <DeckList decks={allDecks} />;
}
```

## Mutations — Server Actions Only

All inserts, updates, and deletes must use Server Actions (`"use server"`). Never use API route handlers for mutations. Server Actions call mutation helpers from `@/db/queries/*` — never use `db` directly.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — inline Drizzle call in a Server Action
"use server";
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decks } from "@/db/schema";

export async function createDeck(data: CreateDeckInput) {
  await db.insert(decks).values({ ...data, userId });
}

// ✅ GOOD — delegates to a query helper
"use server";
import { insertDeck } from "@/db/queries/decks";

export async function createDeck(data: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = createDeckSchema.parse(data);
  const { userId } = await auth();
  return insertDeck({ ...parsed, userId: userId! });
}
```

## Validation — Zod with TypeScript Types

Every Server Action must validate input with a Zod schema. Derive the TypeScript type from the schema using `z.infer`. Never use `FormData` as a parameter type.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — FormData parameter, no validation
async function createDeck(formData: FormData) {
  const title = formData.get("title") as string;
}

// ✅ GOOD — Zod schema with inferred type
import { z } from "zod";

const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1).max(255),
  description: z.string().optional(),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;

async function createDeck(data: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = createDeckSchema.parse(data);
  // use parsed.title, parsed.description
}
```

## Rules Summary

- `db` and Drizzle table imports belong **only** in `src/db/queries/*.ts` files.
- Server Components and Server Actions import from `@/db/queries/*`, never from `@/db` directly.
- One query file per domain entity: `decks.ts`, `cards.ts`, etc.
- Query helpers handle all ownership-scoped filtering (accept `userId` as a parameter).
- For child entities (e.g., `cards` → `decks`), read helpers must `innerJoin` the parent table and filter on `userId` to enforce ownership.
- Keep query helpers pure data access — no auth checks or validation inside them. Auth and validation stay in the calling Server Component or Server Action.
